From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] setup.py: support OE cross builds (interpreter + sysroot)

Four OE-specific tweaks to setup.py's CmakeBuild:

  1. Trust sys.executable for the build interpreter -- upstream's
     get_python_execute() walks sysconfig include paths which, in a
     cross build, point at the *target* Python rather than the
     native one we want to run during the build.

  2. Forward the sysroot from --sysroot= in CC/CXX so find_package
     resolves headers/libs against the staged sysroot, not the
     build host's /. Also pin Protobuf_LIBRARY to the target
     sysroot to avoid FindProtobuf picking up the native protobuf.

  3. Pass -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON to setup.py's CMake invocation.
     setup.py's CmakeBuild runs an independent cmake build in
     ${ONNX_ROOT}/.setuptools-cmake-build/ that produces the
     onnx_cpp2py_export.abi3.so packaged in the Python wheel.
     Without this flag, BUILD_SHARED_LIBS defaults OFF and libonnx
     is built as a static archive; target_link_libraries(
     onnx_cpp2py_export PRIVATE onnx) then pulls the whole static
     onnx archive -- including the protoc-generated
     descriptor_table_* objects -- into the Python C extension.
     The duplicate descriptors are registered twice at load time
     (once by libonnx.so, once by onnx_cpp2py_export.abi3.so) and
     libprotobuf aborts with "File already exists in database:
     onnx/onnx-ml.proto" whenever a process imports both onnx and
     onnxruntime.

  4. Pass -DCMAKE_SKIP_BUILD_RPATH=ON. With BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON the
     cpp2py_export.cc dynamic-links the just-built libonnx.so in
     .setuptools-cmake-build/, so CMake records that path in the
     binary's RPATH for build-tree-run-time usage. setuptools then
     copies the .so straight into the wheel without an install step
     that would have stripped that RPATH, and OE's package_qa fails
     on the buildpath leak. Skipping the build RPATH leaves the .so
     with no embedded path; at runtime on the target, the dynamic
     linker resolves libonnx.so.1.20 from the default search paths
     (/usr/lib is in DT_RUNPATH-less default search).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>

diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -95,20 +95,8 @@


 def get_python_execute():
-    if WINDOWS:
-        return sys.executable
-    # Try to search more accurate path, because sys.executable may return a wrong one,
-    # as discussed in https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/84399
-    python_dir = os.path.abspath(
-        os.path.join(sysconfig.get_path("include"), "..", "..")
-    )
-    if os.path.isdir(python_dir):
-        python_bin = os.path.join(python_dir, "bin", "python3")
-        if os.path.isfile(python_bin):
-            return python_bin
-        python_bin = os.path.join(python_dir, "bin", "python")
-        if os.path.isfile(python_bin):
-            return python_bin
+    # In cross builds, sysconfig points at target paths while sys.executable
+    # is the host-runnable native interpreter — trust it.
     return sys.executable


@@ -174,7 +162,56 @@
                 f"-DPython3_EXECUTABLE={get_python_execute()}",
                 "-DONNX_BUILD_PYTHON=ON",
                 f"-DONNX_NAMESPACE={ONNX_NAMESPACE}",
+                # Build libonnx as SHARED so onnx_cpp2py_export dynamic-links
+                # against it. Without this, BUILD_SHARED_LIBS defaults OFF and
+                # target_link_libraries(onnx_cpp2py_export PRIVATE onnx) pulls
+                # the entire static onnx archive -- including the protoc-
+                # generated descriptor_table_* objects -- into the Python C
+                # extension. The duplicate static initializers then abort
+                # libprotobuf with "File already exists in database:
+                # onnx/onnx-ml.proto" when a process loads both libonnx.so
+                # (e.g. via onnxruntime) and onnx_cpp2py_export.abi3.so.
+                "-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON",
+                # Don't bake the build-tree libonnx.so path into the C
+                # extension's RPATH. CMake otherwise records the
+                # .setuptools-cmake-build directory so the binary can find
+                # libonnx.so at build-tree-run-time; setuptools then copies
+                # the .so straight into the wheel without an install step
+                # that would have stripped it. OE's package_qa fails on
+                # the resulting buildpath leak. The dynamic linker will
+                # still find /usr/lib/libonnx.so.1.20 via default search
+                # paths at runtime on the target.
+                "-DCMAKE_SKIP_BUILD_RPATH=ON",
             ]
+            # Forward cross-build sysroot from CC/CXX so find_package can locate
+            # headers/libs in the staged sysroot rather than the build host's /.
+            import re as _re
+            _sysroot = ""
+            for _v in ("CC", "CXX"):
+                _m = _re.search(r"--sysroot=(\S+)", os.environ.get(_v, ""))
+                if _m:
+                    _sysroot = _m.group(1)
+                    break
+            if _sysroot:
+                _roots = [_sysroot]
+                _native = os.path.join(
+                    os.path.dirname(_sysroot), "recipe-sysroot-native"
+                )
+                if os.path.isdir(_native):
+                    _roots.append(_native)
+                cmake_args += [
+                    f"-DCMAKE_SYSROOT={_sysroot}",
+                    "-DCMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH=" + ";".join(_roots),
+                    "-DCMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_INCLUDE=ONLY",
+                    "-DCMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_LIBRARY=ONLY",
+                    "-DCMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_PACKAGE=ONLY",
+                    "-DCMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_PROGRAM=NEVER",
+                ]
+                # Pin protobuf to the target sysroot — otherwise FindProtobuf
+                # may resolve through protobuf-native (wrong arch).
+                _proto = os.path.join(_sysroot, "usr/lib/libprotobuf.so")
+                if os.path.isfile(_proto):
+                    cmake_args.append(f"-DProtobuf_LIBRARY={_proto}")
             if USE_NINJA and not WINDOWS and shutil.which("ninja"):
                 cmake_args.append("-DCMAKE_GENERATOR=Ninja")

